      • getHexString

        public HexString getHexString​(long index,
                              int length)
                       throws IOException
        Read a hexadecimal String from the TMD file. Mostly stolen from: Stackoverflow (modified)
        Parameters:
        index - The start of the hexadecimal String in the file. (eg. offset 0x140)
        length - The length of the hexadecimal String in the file. (eg. 40 bytes)
        Returns:
        A HexString in format "0x0123456789ABCDEF".
        Throws:
        IOException - An error occurred while reading the TMD file.
